main event: A pilot spotted a rectangular, flat-topped object that became smaller as the aircraft approached King City, California.
interesting points: The object was about 1 mile wide.
The object disappeared when the aircraft was over King City.
The report states 'insufficient data to evaluate'.
There is an additional report of a bright, round object about 40-50 feet in diameter, moving toward Los Angeles at an estimated 20,000 feet altitude.
The second report was submitted by a civilian who was informed of the incident by a flight service center.
sighted object: Rectangular, flat-topped object; bright, round object about 40-50 feet in diameter
location: King City, California; Big Sur, California
witnesses: Pilot; civilian informed by flight service center
